🏨 Built a hotel rate predictor for revenue teams.

Three weeks. Fully containerized. Open source.

What you see:
   → Booking attributes in → predicted rate out
   → ₹9,750 prediction with ±₹500 confidence range
   → Range based on the model's actual MAE on test data
   → Prediction history + trend visualization
   → Built for revenue managers, not data scientists

The stack:
   🐳 Docker Compose (multi-container)
   ⚡ FastAPI (model serving)
   📊 Streamlit (UI)
   🌲 Random Forest + XGBoost (two trained models)
   📐 YAML config-driven preprocessing engine

The architectural decision that mattered:

I built ONE generic preprocessing engine that reads YAML configs,
not separate code per model. Adding a third forecast type
(occupancy, RevPAR, etc.) is now a config file — not a refactor.

The transparency I'm most proud of:
The UI shows the model's MAE (±₹500) right next to the prediction.
Revenue managers shouldn't pretend ML is magic. They need to know
the error bars so they can make defensible pricing decisions.

Built on AtliQ Grands synthetic data — patterns translate directly
to real hotel chains.

Next: HuggingFace Spaces deployment so anyone can try it live.

